
⸻

FG-441 — Merits Brief “Raised • Ruled • Relief” Card
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Even at merits, structure by what was raised, ruled, and what you seek.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Table: Issue • Raised (pin) • Ruled (quote/line) • Relief (two lines). Attach to front matter.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 3-row merits raised/ruled/relief card.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Harm — Dkt 14:3 — ‘Not reached’ (Dkt 18:2) — Relief: remand 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Maps beat long prose.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A 3-row card with one gap cell in red.

⸻

FG-442 — Merits TOC as Answer Sheet
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Your TOC should read like a series of answers.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Rewrite headings as holdings (≤12 words); mirror bookmarks; delete filler subheads.
	•	📝 Assignment: Rewrite 3 TOC headings as answers.
	•	✅ Model Response: “I. Courts must reach harm findings. II. Skipped factors prejudice outcome.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: TOC = roadmap for skim-readers.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A TOC page with bold answer-style lines.

⸻

FG-443 — Merits Pin Atlas (Case • Cite • Pin)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Build an atlas for all citations in one table.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Columns: Case • Cite • Pin/line • Holding (≤10 words). Attach as addendum; hash file.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 6-row pin atlas for your merits brief.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Winter, 555 U.S. 7 — factor findings required — p.12.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Atlases turn cites into maps.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A grid of case names with pins.

⸻

FG-444 — Merits “Two-Pin” Statement of the Case
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Case statements should be two pins, not two pages.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Anchor pin (judgment/order) + Gap pin (skipped line). End with 2-line relief.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 2-pin statement for your case.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Judgment 09/01 (Dkt 88). ‘Not reached’ (Dkt 18:2). Relief: remand 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Economy = persuasion.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two dots → one order line.

⸻

FG-445 — Merits Relief Ladder (Grant • Vacate • Remand • Clarify)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Always offer four doors.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Card: Grant (reverse), Vacate (wipe judgment), Remand (findings), Clarify (fix line). Add scope line.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft your 4-door relief ladder.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Grant (wrong test). Vacate judgment. Remand 21d for findings. Clarify n.3 (‘not reached’). Scope: ¶3 only.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Four doors cover every posture.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Four arrows into a single signature strip.

⸻

FG-446 — Merits OA Prep Grid
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Arguments at merits are still a grid.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Q • Std • 2 pins • Relief; one palm card; hash.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft your OA grid card for merits.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Q: Must courts reach findings? Std: abuse. Pins: Dkt 18:2; Tab 3 p.2. Relief: remand 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Grids survive nerves.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A palm card with 4 blocks.

⸻

FG-447 — Merits Oral Argument Heatmap
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Track what the Justices focus on.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Columns: Justice • Topic • Pin • Minutes • Relief hook. Highlight hot rows; close on them.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 6-row heatmap skeleton.
	•	✅ Model Response: “J3 — 8m on ‘not reached’ (Dkt 18:2). Close: remand 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Heat directs energy.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A heatmap with one row glowing red.

⸻

FG-448 — Merits “Raised/Skipped” Sidebar
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Put the omissions in a visual box.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Sidebar: Issue • Raised (pin) • Skipped (line); one row per factor. Relief: remand.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 4-row sidebar table.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Harm — Dkt 14:3 — Skipped Dkt 18:2 — Relief: remand 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Sidebars beat footnotes.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A margin table with red “Skipped” cells.

⸻

FG-449 — Merits Reply “Two-Paragraph Fit”
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Replies should fix fit in two tight paragraphs.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: ¶1: Misfit between precedent and case. ¶2: Record gap + relief. ≤900 words.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 2-paragraph reply skeleton.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Resp says no split; Atlas shows split. Court skipped harm (Dkt 18:2). Relief: remand 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Short replies earn respect.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two stacked blocks with a red gap pin.

⸻

FG-450 — Merits Phase Closeout Bundle
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Archive merits before judgment.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: ZIP root: Brief.pdf; Reply.pdf; Appendix.pdf; OA cards; CHECKSUMS.txt; ReleaseNote.md. Post mirrors; hash.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build merits closeout ZIP + release note.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Release v5—Merits kit posted: Brief (sha …), Reply (sha …), Appendix (sha …). Mirrors aligned.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Bundles preserve lineage.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A ribboned ZIP with fingerprint tag.